dc_description_s: This ESRI Geodatabase contains polygon features and attribute data tables for 45 layers of census data for the country of Argentina. The data is derived from the Instituto Nacional de Estadistica y Censos de la Republica Argentina (INDEC) and was released in 2010. The data contain 545 census boundary polygons that each have 451 attributes, and the lowest administrative boundary level represented is Departmentos. Refer to the documentation for a list of variables and a translation of variable titles into English. For more information on the census methodology and a glossary of variable categories, go to the INDEC website at http://www.indec.mecon.ar/.
